    • updateQuestion

      public void updateQuestion​(java.lang.String question, java.lang.String option1, java.lang.String option2, java.lang.String option3, java.lang.String option4, byte currentQuestion)
      It passes the question that will be shown to the PlayContent class (window will be shown during the match). see QuestionArea.updateQuestion(String, String, String, String, String, String, byte)
      It updates PriceTable also (the table that show question order and its prize).
      It reset the timer and enable the possible actions like select an answer or the life lines button and withdraw button.
      Parameters:
      question - is a question text.
      option1 - is the first possible alternative.
      option2 - is the second possible alternative.
      option3 - is the third possible alternative.
      option4 - is the fourth possible alternative.
      currentQuestion - is a number that refer to question order.

    • setOptionButtonState

      public void setOptionButtonState​(char optionButtonSymbol, int OptionButtonState)
      It set Option button state. see QuestionArea.setOptionButtonState(char, int)
      Parameters:
      optionButtonSymbol - refers to an option button(A,B,C,D).
      OptionButtonState - refers to a state that an option button will have.

    • enableActions

      private void enableActions()
      Enable the possible actions in different view classes. If its enabled the player can click on the withdrawbutton, the lifelines and select the answer.

    • disableActions

      public void disableActions()
      Disable the possible actions in different view classes. It is needed to prevent the player to click the withdrawbutton after selecting a wrong answer, prevent the player to change answer and prevent the player to select the lifelines.

    • setLifeLineHint

      public void setLifeLineHint​(java.lang.String hint, byte currentQuestion)
      Push the hint forward, reset timer, enable actions and play a sound.
      Parameters:
      hint - a text that will be shown as a life line hint.
      currentQuestion - is a number that refer to question order.

    • showEndGameScreen

      public void showEndGameScreen​(java.lang.String playerName, java.lang.String playerBalance, java.lang.String gameDate)
      It shows EndGameScreen (the screen that will show money check with player information (name, balance,game date))
      Parameters:
      playerName - refers to player name that was entered of the player at game start.
      playerBalance - refers to the balance (prize) that player got.
      gameDate - refers to game date.
